We are given a two-dimensional board for a snake game represented by a grid of characters:  '+'  an impassable square (the snake cannot move through it)  '0'  a passable square (the snake can move through it)  Snakes may enter only from the edges of the board and move in a straight line either horizontally or vertically. Our goal is to identify which rows and columns are completely passable, meaning they contain only '0' characters  allowing a snake to move straight through the entire board from one side to the other.
